<Component name="Architecture">
  <VStack padding="$space-4" gap="$space-4">

    <Card title="Bram"
          subtitle="A Tauri shell with a real PTY on the left and two iframes on the right: the project under development plus an agent-tools drawer">
      <Text>
        The Rust backend owns the PTY, a custom tauri:// URI scheme
        handler that proxies the right pane to the project's HTTP server
        and serves shell assets, and a filesystem watcher that triggers
        iframe reloads. The web parent (main.js) bridges xterm.js and
        both iframes.
      </Text>
      <Text>
        Two iframes load same-origin with the parent at tauri://localhost:
        the **right pane** (the project under development — any web app:
        a React/Vue/Svelte SPA, a static site, an XMLUI app, etc.) and
        the **agent-tools drawer** (Bram's own control surface,
        an XMLUI app built into the binary at app/tools/, providing the
        Transcript, Worklist, Commits, Issues, Sessions, Context, and
        README tabs). Because both share an origin with the parent,
        iframe code calls Tauri IPC directly via
        window.parent.__TAURI__.core.invoke — no postMessage bridge for
        routine calls. Voice is the lone exception, because the parent
        shell owns the MediaRecorder pipeline.
      </Text>
    </Card>

    <Card title="Data flow">
      <EChart
        height="560px"
        option="{{
          tooltip: { show: true, formatter: function(p) { return p.dataType === 'edge' ? p.data.value : p.data.name; } },
          animation: false,
          series: [{
            type: 'graph',
            layout: 'none',
            roam: true,
            symbol: 'roundRect',
            symbolSize: [150, 56],
            label: { show: true, fontSize: 12, color: '#fff', fontWeight: 'bold' },
            edgeLabel: { show: true, fontSize: 10, formatter: '{c}' },
            edgeSymbol: ['none', 'arrow'],
            edgeSymbolSize: [4, 9],
            lineStyle: { opacity: 0.85, width: 1.5, curveness: 0.05 },
            data: [
              { name: 'User',                 x: 420, y: 30,  itemStyle: { color: '#666' } },
              { name: 'Terminal (xterm.js)',  x: 150, y: 150, itemStyle: { color: '#0b6' } },
              { name: 'Right pane + agent-tools iframes', x: 690, y: 150, symbolSize: [200, 56], itemStyle: { color: '#06b' } },
              { name: 'Parent shell main.js', x: 420, y: 280, itemStyle: { color: '#444' } },
              { name: 'Rust / Tauri backend', x: 420, y: 410, itemStyle: { color: '#a40' } },
              { name: 'Claude / Codex CLI',   x: 420, y: 540, itemStyle: { color: '#840' } }
            ],
            links: [
              { source: 'User',                 target: 'Terminal (xterm.js)',  value: 'keystrokes' },
              { source: 'User',                 target: 'Right pane + agent-tools iframes',         value: 'clicks / sees' },
              { source: 'Terminal (xterm.js)',  target: 'Parent shell main.js', value: 'term.onData' },
              { source: 'Parent shell main.js', target: 'Terminal (xterm.js)', value: 'term.write', lineStyle: { curveness: -0.2 } },
              { source: 'Right pane + agent-tools iframes',         target: 'Rust / Tauri backend', value: 'invoke() via window.parent.__TAURI__' },
              { source: 'Parent shell main.js', target: 'Right pane + agent-tools iframes',         value: 'iframe.src reload', lineStyle: { curveness: -0.2 } },
              { source: 'Parent shell main.js', target: 'Rust / Tauri backend', value: 'invoke()' },
              { source: 'Rust / Tauri backend', target: 'Parent shell main.js', value: 'Channel + emit', lineStyle: { curveness: -0.2 } },
              { source: 'Rust / Tauri backend', target: 'Right pane + agent-tools iframes',         value: 'event.listen() (file watcher, etc.)', lineStyle: { curveness: 0.15 } },
              { source: 'Rust / Tauri backend', target: 'Claude / Codex CLI',   value: 'PTY stdin' },
              { source: 'Claude / Codex CLI',   target: 'Rust / Tauri backend', value: 'PTY stdout', lineStyle: { curveness: -0.2 } }
            ]
          }]
        }}" />
    </Card>

    <Tabs>
      <TabItem label="Four layers">
        <VStack gap="$space-3" padding="$space-3">
          <Card title="1. Rust / Tauri backend"
                subtitle="src-tauri/src/lib.rs">
            <Text>
              Owns the PTY (portable_pty), spawns the child shell with the
              project root as cwd, streams stdout to JS via a
              tauri::ipc::Channel, accepts stdin via pty_write. Registers a
              custom tauri:// URI scheme handler whose four routing tiers
              are: /__project/* proxied to the project's HTTP server,
              shell assets served from app/ under /__shell/, /__vendor/,
              /__tools/, every other /__* path forwarded to the same
              loopback tiny_http server, and everything else returning the
              embedded index.html. Spawns a notify watcher that emits
              scoped reload events plus targeted state-changed events
              (talk-session-changed, pty-menu-changed, worklist-changed,
              etc.). Also handles trace export, url opening, voice
              transcription via whisper.cpp.
            </Text>
          </Card>
          <Card title="2. Parent shell (web)"
                subtitle="app/index.html + app/main.js">
            <Text>
              The window's host page. Mounts xterm.js into the left pane,
              mounts both iframes at tauri://localhost. Bridges terminal
              keystrokes → PTY and PTY output → terminal; owns the voice
              MediaRecorder pipeline. Re-assigns iframe.src in response to
              file-watcher reload events. Iframe code calls Tauri IPC
              directly without going through main.js, so the parent's
              iframe-facing surface is intentionally small.
            </Text>
          </Card>
          <Card title="3. Right pane — the app under development"
                subtitle="any web app served from the project root via /__project/*">
            <Text>
              Whatever's at the project root: a React/Vue/Svelte SPA, a
              static site, a server-rendered app, an XMLUI app — anything
              the project's HTTP server (declared in `.bram.json`
              with legacy `.xmlui-desktop.json` fallback
              or auto-detected) returns. The scheme handler proxies
              /__project/* to that server, so the iframe's
              location.origin is tauri://localhost while the bytes come
              from 127.0.0.1:&lt;random-port&gt;. Project code that wants
              to talk back to Bram opts in by including
              app/__shell/helpers.js, which exposes window.toShell,
              window.toTurn, window.sendKeys, window.logToHost,
              window.openExternal, window.captureScreenshot,
              window.gitPush, and window.subscribeRightPaneSize — thin
              getTauriInvoke() wrappers that call IPC commands directly.
            </Text>
          </Card>
          <Card title="4. Agent-tools drawer — Bram's own control surface"
                subtitle="app/tools/Main.xmlui + components, built into the binary">
            <Text>
              The second iframe (toggled from the toolbar) and the only
              piece guaranteed to be XMLUI. Ships with the binary at
              app/tools/, loads helpers.js unconditionally, and renders
              the Transcript, Worklist, Commits, Issues, Sessions,
              Context, and README tabs. Uses Tauri IPC and the loopback
              /__* HTTP routes for everything; subscribes to file-watcher
              events directly via window.parent.__TAURI__.event.listen
              for live updates.
            </Text>
          </Card>
        </VStack>
      </TabItem>

      <TabItem label="Rust IPC commands">
        <Table data="{[
          { name: 'pty_spawn',           purpose: 'Open a PTY, spawn the shell, stream output via Channel' },
          { name: 'pty_write',           purpose: 'Write bytes to the PTY (typed input or right-pane injection)' },
          { name: 'pty_resize',          purpose: 'Resize the PTY when xterm reflows' },
          { name: 'log_from_right_pane', purpose: 'Forward iframe log payloads to cargo run stderr' },
          { name: 'open_devtools',       purpose: 'Open the webview devtools (debug builds)' },
          { name: 'open_url',            purpose: 'Open an external URL with the host OS opener' },
          { name: 'save_trace_export',   purpose: 'Write an Inspector trace export to ~/Downloads' }
        ]}">
          <Column bindTo="name"    header="Command" width="280px" />
          <Column bindTo="purpose" header="Purpose" />
        </Table>
      </TabItem>

      <TabItem label="Iframe → host IPC">
        <VStack gap="$space-3" padding="$space-3">
          <Text>
            Iframe code (right pane and agent-tools drawer) calls Tauri
            IPC directly through window.parent.__TAURI__.core.invoke.
            app/__shell/helpers.js wraps the common commands as window
            globals so XMLUI components can call them from event handlers:
          </Text>
          <Table data="{[
            { helper: 'toShell(text)',          ipc: 'pty_write — text + \n into the PTY (like typing it)' },
            { helper: 'toTurn(text)',           ipc: 'pty_write — bracketed-paste markers + CR (one Claude/Codex turn)' },
            { helper: 'sendKeys(text)',         ipc: 'pty_write — raw bytes, no newline (Esc, arrows, single-keypress menus)' },
            { helper: 'logToHost(payload)',     ipc: 'log_from_right_pane — forwards to cargo run stderr (silent to the agent)' },
            { helper: 'openExternal(url)',      ipc: 'open_url — opens via the host OS opener' },
            { helper: 'captureScreenshot()',    ipc: 'capture_screenshot — then injects @path via toTurn' },
            { helper: 'gitPush(commitsDs)',     ipc: 'git_push — and refetches the commits DataSource on success' },
            { helper: 'inspector-export listener', ipc: 'save_trace_export — writes the Inspector trace JSON to ~/Downloads' }
          ]}">
            <Column bindTo="helper" header="helper" width="260px" />
            <Column bindTo="ipc"    header="Tauri command" />
          </Table>
          <Text>
            Include from any project's index.html with
            &lt;script src="tauri://localhost/__shell/helpers.js"&gt;.
            getRightPaneSize / subscribeRightPaneSize are also exposed,
            but they don't hit IPC — same-origin iframes read their own
            viewport via window.innerWidth / innerHeight, with a window
            "resize" listener for the continuous variant.
          </Text>
          <Text>
            Voice (voiceStart, voiceStop) is the one helper that still
            posts to main.js — the parent shell owns the MediaRecorder
            pipeline and the single-in-flight rejection logic.
          </Text>
        </VStack>
      </TabItem>

      <TabItem label="Hot reload + tauri://">
        <VStack gap="$space-3" padding="$space-3">
          <Card title="Why a custom URI scheme">
            <Text>
              Tauri's bundled-frontend protocol stamps unknown extensions
              as text/html, which xmlui-standalone rejects. The tauri://
              handler in lib.rs serves shell assets from app/ with the
              correct MIME types (including .xmlui and .xs as text/plain
              so they load), and proxies /__project/* to the project's
              HTTP server so the right pane shares an origin with the
              parent. It also sets Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *.
            </Text>
          </Card>
          <Card title="Same-origin reload">
            <Text>
              Both iframes are same-origin with the parent now, so
              iframe.contentWindow.location.reload() works in principle —
              but reassigning iframe.src with a ?t= cache-buster gives
              the file watcher cleaner control over which iframes reload
              on which path-prefix changes (app/__shell/ and app/vendor/
              reload both, app/tools/ reloads the drawer only, the
              project directory reloads the right pane only).
            </Text>
          </Card>
        </VStack>
      </TabItem>

    </Tabs>

  </VStack>
</Component>
